ozwell.s1: The two notes are very similar as they both describe the same medical case involving a 20-year-old female patient with a deformity and bulging in the anterior chest wall, suspected to be a tumor. Both notes detail the diagnostic workup, including a chest X-ray, CT scan, core needle biopsy, and incisional biopsy, leading to a final diagnosis of an aneurysmal bone cyst. They also describe the treatment plan involving a total sternectomy and the surgical procedure, including the use of a cryopreserved sternal allograft for repair. Postoperative findings and follow-up recommendations are also consistent in both notes. The main difference is in the format and some specific details, such as the inclusion of figures and the exact wording used.
